The paper deals with the study of self-adjusting data structures, specifically self-adjusting complete trees, which are a type of binary tree. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also discusses the use of these trees in warehouse optimization and self-adjusting communication networks, which could fall under the categories of data mining (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), networked systems (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
